  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 17 high, 7 medium, 15 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 14 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, thunderstorm / convective risk and mist  — most notably around Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Warsaw Chopin (WAW/EPWA) and Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ). Network hotspots: Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Birmingham (BHX/EGBB), Glasgow (GLA/EGPF) and 3 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Olsztyn-Mazury (SZY/EPSY) and 9 others.",
